The paper deals with natural image matting, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and dilated convolutions, which are common techniques in image processing and computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the importance of fine structures like hair, which is relevant to multimedia applications (cs.MM). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG), and the paper also discusses the use of adversarial loss in training the network, which is a common technique in GANs. Finally, the paper discusses the improvement of existing encoder-decoder architectures, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
